1.Now all the controller methods are accessible respect the users roles in their database for
achieving Custom Role allotment Feature(admin);

2.The roles of the user from SecurityContextHolder and Their database will be compared , if it is same then only user
can access the requested endpoint. If suddenly UserRole has been changed(Due Hacked or UnAuthorized Access) in database or SecurityHolder
It may throw Forbidden or UnAuthorized Error.

3.It it occurs We can create a service to make both role are same. It provide More Security to our application.
NOTE: If hackers try to hack,they may have to hack SecurityContextHolder And as well as Database and they may hack an endpoint that make roles to be same.




